34class MyFlushBlockPolicy : public FlushBlockPolicy {
35 public:
36 explicit MyFlushBlockPolicy(const int num_keys_in_block,
37 const BlockBuilder& data_block_builder)
38 : num_keys_in_block_(num_keys_in_block),
39 num_keys_(0),
40 data_block_builder_(data_block_builder) {}
41
42 bool Update(const Slice& /*key*/, const Slice& /*value*/) override {
43 if (data_block_builder_.empty()) {
44 // First key in this block
45 num_keys_ = 1;
46 return false;
47 }
48 // Flush every 10 keys
49 if (num_keys_ == num_keys_in_block_) {
50 num_keys_ = 1;
51 return true;
52 }
53 num_keys_++;
54 return false;
55 }
56
57 private:
58 const int num_keys_in_block_;
59 int num_keys_;
60 const BlockBuilder& data_block_builder_;
61};
62
63class MyFlushBlockPolicyFactory : public FlushBlockPolicyFactory {
64 public:
65 explicit MyFlushBlockPolicyFactory(const int num_keys_in_block)
66 : num_keys_in_block_(num_keys_in_block) {}
67
68 virtual const char* Name() const override {
69 return "MyFlushBlockPolicyFactory";
70 }
71
72 virtual FlushBlockPolicy* NewFlushBlockPolicy(
73 const BlockBasedTableOptions& /*table_options*/,
74 const BlockBuilder& data_block_builder) const override {
75 return new MyFlushBlockPolicy(num_keys_in_block_, data_block_builder);
76 }
77
78 private:
79 const int num_keys_in_block_;
80};
81} // namespace

125TEST_F(DBBasicTest, UniqueSession) {
126 Options options = CurrentOptions();
127 std::string sid1, sid2, sid3, sid4;
128
129 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid1));
130 Reopen(options);
131 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid2));
132 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "v1"));
133 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid4));
134 Reopen(options);
135 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid3));
136
137 ASSERT_NE(sid1, sid2);
138 ASSERT_NE(sid1, sid3);
139 ASSERT_NE(sid2, sid3);
140
141 ASSERT_EQ(sid2, sid4);
142
143 // Expected compact format for session ids (see notes in implementation)
144 TestRegex expected("[0-9A-Z]{20}");
145 EXPECT_MATCHES_REGEX(sid1, expected);
146 EXPECT_MATCHES_REGEX(sid2, expected);
147 EXPECT_MATCHES_REGEX(sid3, expected);
148
149 Close();
150 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
151 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid1));
152 // Test uniqueness between readonly open (sid1) and regular open (sid3)
153 ASSERT_NE(sid1, sid3);
154 Close();
155 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
156 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid2));
157 ASSERT_EQ("v1", Get("foo"));
158 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid3));
159
160 ASSERT_NE(sid1, sid2);
161
162 ASSERT_EQ(sid2, sid3);
163
164 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"goku"}, options);
165 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid1));
166 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "e1"));
167 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid2));
168 ASSERT_EQ("e1", Get("bar"));
169 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid3));
170 ReopenWithColumnFamilies({"default", "goku"}, options);
171 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbSessionId(sid4));
172
173 ASSERT_EQ(sid1, sid2);
174 ASSERT_EQ(sid2, sid3);
175
176 ASSERT_NE(sid1, sid4);
177}

179TEST_F(DBBasicTest, ReadOnlyDB) {
180 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "v1"));
181 ASSERT_OK(Put("bar", "v2"));
182 ASSERT_OK(Put("foo", "v3"));
183 Close();
184
185 auto verify_one_iter = [&](Iterator* iter) {
186 int count = 0;
187 for (iter->SeekToFirst(); iter->Valid(); iter->Next()) {
188 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
189 ++count;
190 }
191 ASSERT_OK(iter->status());
192 // Always expect two keys: "foo" and "bar"
193 ASSERT_EQ(count, 2);
194 };
195
196 auto verify_all_iters = [&]() {
197 Iterator* iter = db_->NewIterator(ReadOptions());
198 verify_one_iter(iter);
199 delete iter;
200
201 std::vector<Iterator*> iters;
202 ASSERT_OK(db_->NewIterators(ReadOptions(),
203 {dbfull()->DefaultColumnFamily()}, &iters));
204 ASSERT_EQ(static_cast<uint64_t>(1), iters.size());
205 verify_one_iter(iters[0]);
206 delete iters[0];
207 };
208
209 auto options = CurrentOptions();
210 assert(options.env == env_);
211 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
212 ASSERT_EQ("v3", Get("foo"));
213 ASSERT_EQ("v2", Get("bar"));
214 verify_all_iters();
215 Close();
216
217 // Reopen and flush memtable.
218 Reopen(options);
219 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
220 Close();
221 // Now check keys in read only mode.
222 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
223 ASSERT_EQ("v3", Get("foo"));
224 ASSERT_EQ("v2", Get("bar"));
225 verify_all_iters();
226 ASSERT_TRUE(db_->SyncWAL().IsNotSupported());
227}

270TEST_F(DBBasicTest, CompactedDB) {
271 const uint64_t kFileSize = 1 << 20;
272 Options options = CurrentOptions();
273 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
274 options.write_buffer_size = kFileSize;
275 options.target_file_size_base = kFileSize;
276 options.max_bytes_for_level_base = 1 << 30;
277 options.compression = kNoCompression;
278 Reopen(options);
279 // 1 L0 file, use CompactedDB if max_open_files = -1
280 ASSERT_OK(Put("aaa", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, '1')));
281 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
282 Close();
283 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
284 Status s = Put("new", "value");
285 ASSERT_EQ(s.ToString(),
286 "Not implemented: Not supported operation in read only mode.");
287 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, '1'), Get("aaa"));
288 Close();
289 options.max_open_files = -1;
290 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
291 s = Put("new", "value");
292 ASSERT_EQ(s.ToString(),
293 "Not implemented: Not supported in compacted db mode.");
294 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, '1'), Get("aaa"));
295 Close();
296 Reopen(options);
297 // Add more L0 files
298 ASSERT_OK(Put("bbb", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, '2')));
299 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
300 ASSERT_OK(Put("aaa", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'a')));
301 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
302 ASSERT_OK(Put("bbb", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'b')));
303 ASSERT_OK(Put("eee", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'e')));
304 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
305 ASSERT_OK(Put("something_not_flushed", "x"));
306 Close();
307
308 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
309 // Fallback to read-only DB
310 s = Put("new", "value");
311 ASSERT_EQ(s.ToString(),
312 "Not implemented: Not supported operation in read only mode.");
313
314 // TODO: validate that other write ops return NotImplemented
315 // (DBImplReadOnly is missing some overrides)
316
317 // Ensure no deadlock on flush triggered by another API function
318 // (Old deadlock bug depends on something_not_flushed above.)
319 std::vector<std::string> files;
320 uint64_t manifest_file_size;
321 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetLiveFiles(files, &manifest_file_size, /*flush*/ true));
322 LiveFilesStorageInfoOptions lfsi_opts;
323 lfsi_opts.wal_size_for_flush = 0; // always
324 std::vector<LiveFileStorageInfo> files2;
325 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetLiveFilesStorageInfo(lfsi_opts, &files2));
326
327 Close();
328
329 // Full compaction
330 Reopen(options);
331 // Add more keys
332 ASSERT_OK(Put("fff", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'f')));
333 ASSERT_OK(Put("hhh", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'h')));
334 ASSERT_OK(Put("iii", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'i')));
335 ASSERT_OK(Put("jjj", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'j')));
336 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
337 ASSERT_EQ(3, NumTableFilesAtLevel(1));
338 Close();
339
340 // CompactedDB
341 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
342 s = Put("new", "value");
343 ASSERT_EQ(s.ToString(),
344 "Not implemented: Not supported in compacted db mode.");
345 ASSERT_EQ("NOT_FOUND", Get("abc"));
346 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'a'), Get("aaa"));
347 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'b'), Get("bbb"));
348 ASSERT_EQ("NOT_FOUND", Get("ccc"));
349 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'e'), Get("eee"));
350 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'f'), Get("fff"));
351 ASSERT_EQ("NOT_FOUND", Get("ggg"));
352 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'h'), Get("hhh"));
353 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'i'), Get("iii"));
354 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'j'), Get("jjj"));
355 ASSERT_EQ("NOT_FOUND", Get("kkk"));
356
357 // TODO: validate that other write ops return NotImplemented
358 // (CompactedDB is missing some overrides)
359
360 // Ensure no deadlock on flush triggered by another API function
361 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetLiveFiles(files, &manifest_file_size, /*flush*/ true));
362 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetLiveFilesStorageInfo(lfsi_opts, &files2));
363
364 // MultiGet
365 std::vector<std::string> values;
366 std::vector<Status> status_list = dbfull()->MultiGet(
367 ReadOptions(),
368 std::vector<Slice>({Slice("aaa"), Slice("ccc"), Slice("eee"),
369 Slice("ggg"), Slice("iii"), Slice("kkk")}),
370 &values);
371 ASSERT_EQ(status_list.size(), static_cast<uint64_t>(6));
372 ASSERT_EQ(values.size(), static_cast<uint64_t>(6));
373 ASSERT_OK(status_list[0]);
374 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'a'), values[0]);
375 ASSERT_TRUE(status_list[1].IsNotFound());
376 ASSERT_OK(status_list[2]);
377 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'e'), values[2]);
378 ASSERT_TRUE(status_list[3].IsNotFound());
379 ASSERT_OK(status_list[4]);
380 ASSERT_EQ(DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'i'), values[4]);
381 ASSERT_TRUE(status_list[5].IsNotFound());
382
383 Reopen(options);
384 // Add a key
385 ASSERT_OK(Put("fff", DummyString(kFileSize / 2, 'f')));
386 Close();
387 ASSERT_OK(ReadOnlyReopen(options));
388 s = Put("new", "value");
389 ASSERT_EQ(s.ToString(),
390 "Not implemented: Not supported operation in read only mode.");
391}

572TEST_F(DBBasicTest, FlushEmptyColumnFamily) {
573 // Block flush thread and disable compaction thread
574 env_->SetBackgroundThreads(1, Env::HIGH);
575 env_->SetBackgroundThreads(1, Env::LOW);
576 test::SleepingBackgroundTask sleeping_task_low;
577 env_->Schedule(&test::SleepingBackgroundTask::DoSleepTask, &sleeping_task_low,
578 Env::Priority::LOW);
579 test::SleepingBackgroundTask sleeping_task_high;
580 env_->Schedule(&test::SleepingBackgroundTask::DoSleepTask,
581 &sleeping_task_high, Env::Priority::HIGH);
582
583 Options options = CurrentOptions();
584 // disable compaction
585 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
586 WriteOptions writeOpt = WriteOptions();
587 writeOpt.disableWAL = true;
588 options.max_write_buffer_number = 2;
589 options.min_write_buffer_number_to_merge = 1;
590 options.max_write_buffer_size_to_maintain =
591 static_cast<int64_t>(options.write_buffer_size);
592 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
593
594 // Compaction can still go through even if no thread can flush the
595 // mem table.
596 ASSERT_OK(Flush(0));
597 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
598
599 // Insert can go through
600 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Put(writeOpt, handles_[0], "foo", "v1"));
601 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Put(writeOpt, handles_[1], "bar", "v1"));
602
603 ASSERT_EQ("v1", Get(0, "foo"));
604 ASSERT_EQ("v1", Get(1, "bar"));
605
606 sleeping_task_high.WakeUp();
607 sleeping_task_high.WaitUntilDone();
608
609 // Flush can still go through.
610 ASSERT_OK(Flush(0));
611 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
612
613 sleeping_task_low.WakeUp();
614 sleeping_task_low.WaitUntilDone();
615}

617TEST_F(DBBasicTest, Flush) {
618 do {
619 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, CurrentOptions());
620 WriteOptions writeOpt = WriteOptions();
621 writeOpt.disableWAL = true;
622 SetPerfLevel(kEnableTime);
623 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->Put(writeOpt, handles_[1], "foo", "v1"));
624 // this will now also flush the last 2 writes
625 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));

687TEST_F(DBBasicTest, IdentityAcrossRestarts) {
688 constexpr size_t kMinIdSize = 10;
689 do {
690 for (bool with_manifest : {false, true}) {
691 for (bool write_file : {false, true}) {
692 std::string idfilename = IdentityFileName(dbname_);
693 std::string id1, tmp;
694 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbIdentity(id1));
695 ASSERT_GE(id1.size(), kMinIdSize);
696
697 Options options = CurrentOptions();
698 options.write_dbid_to_manifest = with_manifest;
699 options.write_identity_file = true; // initially
700 Reopen(options);
701 std::string id2;
702 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbIdentity(id2));
703 // id2 should match id1 because identity was not regenerated
704 ASSERT_EQ(id1, id2);
705 ASSERT_OK(ReadFileToString(env_, idfilename, &tmp));
706 ASSERT_EQ(tmp, id2);
707
708 if (write_file) {
709 // Recover from deleted/missing IDENTITY
710 ASSERT_OK(env_->DeleteFile(idfilename));
711 } else {
712 // Transition to no IDENTITY file
713 options.write_identity_file = false;
714 if (!with_manifest) {
715 // Incompatible options, should fail
716 ASSERT_NOK(TryReopen(options));
717 // Back to a usable config and continue
718 options.write_identity_file = true;
719 Reopen(options);
720 continue;
721 }
722 }
723 Reopen(options);
724 std::string id3;
725 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbIdentity(id3));
726 if (with_manifest) {
727 // id3 should match id1 because identity was restored from manifest
728 ASSERT_EQ(id1, id3);
729 } else {
730 // id3 should NOT match id1 because identity was regenerated
731 ASSERT_NE(id1, id3);
732 ASSERT_GE(id3.size(), kMinIdSize);
733 }
734 if (write_file) {
735 ASSERT_OK(ReadFileToString(env_, idfilename, &tmp));
736 ASSERT_EQ(tmp, id3);
737
738 // Recover from truncated IDENTITY
739 std::unique_ptr<WritableFile> w;
740 ASSERT_OK(env_->NewWritableFile(idfilename, &w, EnvOptions()));
741 ASSERT_OK(w->Close());
742 } else {
743 ASSERT_TRUE(env_->FileExists(idfilename).IsNotFound());
744 }
745 Reopen(options);
746 std::string id4;
747 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbIdentity(id4));
748 if (with_manifest) {
749 // id4 should match id1 because identity was restored from manifest
750 ASSERT_EQ(id1, id4);
751 } else {
752 // id4 should NOT match id1 because identity was regenerated
753 ASSERT_NE(id1, id4);
754 ASSERT_GE(id4.size(), kMinIdSize);
755 }
756 std::string silly_id = "asdf123456789";
757 if (write_file) {
758 ASSERT_OK(ReadFileToString(env_, idfilename, &tmp));
759 ASSERT_EQ(tmp, id4);
760
761 // Recover from overwritten IDENTITY
762 std::unique_ptr<WritableFile> w;
763 ASSERT_OK(env_->NewWritableFile(idfilename, &w, EnvOptions()));
764 ASSERT_OK(w->Append(silly_id));
765 ASSERT_OK(w->Close());
766 } else {
767 ASSERT_TRUE(env_->FileExists(idfilename).IsNotFound());
768 }
769 Reopen(options);
770 std::string id5;
771 ASSERT_OK(db_->GetDbIdentity(id5));
772 if (with_manifest) {
773 // id4 should match id1 because identity was restored from manifest
774 ASSERT_EQ(id1, id5);
775 } else {
776 ASSERT_EQ(id5, silly_id);
777 }
778 if (write_file) {
779 ASSERT_OK(ReadFileToString(env_, idfilename, &tmp));
780 ASSERT_EQ(tmp, id5);
781 } else {
782 ASSERT_TRUE(env_->FileExists(idfilename).IsNotFound());
783 }
784 }
785 }
786 } while (ChangeCompactOptions());
787}

811 env_->SetMockSleep();
812 anon::OptionsOverride options_override;
813 options_override.skip_policy = kSkipNoSnapshot;
814 do {
815 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, CurrentOptions(options_override));
816 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, "foo", "0v1"));
817 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "1v1"));
818
819 const Snapshot* s1 = db_->GetSnapshot();
820 ASSERT_EQ(1U, GetNumSnapshots());
821 uint64_t time_snap1 = GetTimeOldestSnapshots();
822 ASSERT_GT(time_snap1, 0U);
823 ASSERT_EQ(GetSequenceOldestSnapshots(), s1->GetSequenceNumber());
824 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, "foo", "0v2"));
825 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "1v2"));
826
827 env_->MockSleepForSeconds(1);
828
829 const Snapshot* s2 = db_->GetSnapshot();
830 ASSERT_EQ(2U, GetNumSnapshots());
831 ASSERT_EQ(time_snap1, GetTimeOldestSnapshots());
832 ASSERT_EQ(GetSequenceOldestSnapshots(), s1->GetSequenceNumber());
833 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, "foo", "0v3"));
834 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "1v3"));
835
836 {
837 ManagedSnapshot s3(db_);
838 ASSERT_EQ(3U, GetNumSnapshots());
839 ASSERT_EQ(time_snap1, GetTimeOldestSnapshots());
840 ASSERT_EQ(GetSequenceOldestSnapshots(), s1->GetSequenceNumber());
841
842 ASSERT_OK(Put(0, "foo", "0v4"));
843 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "1v4"));
844 ASSERT_EQ("0v1", Get(0, "foo", s1));
845 ASSERT_EQ("1v1", Get(1, "foo", s1));
846 ASSERT_EQ("0v2", Get(0, "foo", s2));
847 ASSERT_EQ("1v2", Get(1, "foo", s2));
848 ASSERT_EQ("0v3", Get(0, "foo", s3.snapshot()));
849 ASSERT_EQ("1v3", Get(1, "foo", s3.snapshot()));
850 ASSERT_EQ("0v4", Get(0, "foo"));
851 ASSERT_EQ("1v4", Get(1, "foo"));
852 }
853
854 ASSERT_EQ(2U, GetNumSnapshots());
855 ASSERT_EQ(time_snap1, GetTimeOldestSnapshots());
856 ASSERT_EQ(GetSequenceOldestSnapshots(), s1->GetSequenceNumber());
857 ASSERT_EQ("0v1", Get(0, "foo", s1));
858 ASSERT_EQ("1v1", Get(1, "foo", s1));
859 ASSERT_EQ("0v2", Get(0, "foo", s2));
860 ASSERT_EQ("1v2", Get(1, "foo", s2));
861 ASSERT_EQ("0v4", Get(0, "foo"));
862 ASSERT_EQ("1v4", Get(1, "foo"));
863
864 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(s1);
865 ASSERT_EQ("0v2", Get(0, "foo", s2));
866 ASSERT_EQ("1v2", Get(1, "foo", s2));
867 ASSERT_EQ("0v4", Get(0, "foo"));
868 ASSERT_EQ("1v4", Get(1, "foo"));
869 ASSERT_EQ(1U, GetNumSnapshots());
870 ASSERT_LT(time_snap1, GetTimeOldestSnapshots());
871 ASSERT_EQ(GetSequenceOldestSnapshots(), s2->GetSequenceNumber());
872
873 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(s2);
874 ASSERT_EQ(0U, GetNumSnapshots());
875 ASSERT_EQ(GetSequenceOldestSnapshots(), 0);
876 ASSERT_EQ("0v4", Get(0, "foo"));
877 ASSERT_EQ("1v4", Get(1, "foo"));
878 } while (ChangeOptions());

898TEST_P(DBBasicMultiConfigs, CompactBetweenSnapshots) {
899 anon::OptionsOverride options_override;
900 options_override.skip_policy = kSkipNoSnapshot;
901 Options options = CurrentOptions(options_override);
902 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
903 DestroyAndReopen(options);
904 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
905 Random rnd(301);
906 FillLevels("a", "z", 1);
907
908 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "first"));
909 const Snapshot* snapshot1 = db_->GetSnapshot();
910 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "second"));
911 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "third"));
912 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "fourth"));
913 const Snapshot* snapshot2 = db_->GetSnapshot();
914 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "fifth"));
915 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "sixth"));
916
917 // All entries (including duplicates) exist
918 // before any compaction or flush is triggered.
919 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1),
920 "[ sixth, fifth, fourth, third, second, first ]");
921 ASSERT_EQ("sixth", Get(1, "foo"));
922 ASSERT_EQ("fourth", Get(1, "foo", snapshot2));
923 ASSERT_EQ("first", Get(1, "foo", snapshot1));
924
925 // After a flush, "second", "third" and "fifth" should
926 // be removed
927 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
928 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ sixth, fourth, first ]");
929
930 // after we release the snapshot1, only two values left
931 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot1);
932 FillLevels("a", "z", 1);
933 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1], nullptr,
934 nullptr));
935
936 // We have only one valid snapshot snapshot2. Since snapshot1 is
937 // not valid anymore, "first" should be removed by a compaction.
938 ASSERT_EQ("sixth", Get(1, "foo"));
939 ASSERT_EQ("fourth", Get(1, "foo", snapshot2));
940 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ sixth, fourth ]");
941
942 // after we release the snapshot2, only one value should be left
943 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot2);
944 FillLevels("a", "z", 1);
945 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1], nullptr,
946 nullptr));
947 ASSERT_EQ("sixth", Get(1, "foo"));
948 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ sixth ]");
949}

994TEST_F(DBBasicTest, CompactOnFlush) {
995 anon::OptionsOverride options_override;
996 options_override.skip_policy = kSkipNoSnapshot;
997 do {
998 Options options = CurrentOptions(options_override);
999 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
1000 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu"}, options);
1001
1002 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v1"));
1003 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1004 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v1 ]");
1005
1006 // Write two new keys
1007 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "a", "begin"));
1008 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "z", "end"));
1009 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1010
1011 // Case1: Delete followed by a put
1012 ASSERT_OK(Delete(1, "foo"));
1013 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v2"));
1014 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v2, DEL, v1 ]");
1015
1016 // After the current memtable is flushed, the DEL should
1017 // have been removed
1018 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1019 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v2, v1 ]");
1020
1021 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1],
1022 nullptr, nullptr));
1023 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v2 ]");
1024
1025 // Case 2: Delete followed by another delete
1026 ASSERT_OK(Delete(1, "foo"));
1027 ASSERT_OK(Delete(1, "foo"));
1028 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ DEL, DEL, v2 ]");
1029 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1030 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ DEL, v2 ]");
1031 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1],
1032 nullptr, nullptr));
1033 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ ]");
1034
1035 // Case 3: Put followed by a delete
1036 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v3"));
1037 ASSERT_OK(Delete(1, "foo"));
1038 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ DEL, v3 ]");
1039 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1040 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ DEL ]");
1041 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1],
1042 nullptr, nullptr));
1043 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ ]");
1044
1045 // Case 4: Put followed by another Put
1046 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v4"));
1047 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v5"));
1048 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v5, v4 ]");
1049 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1050 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v5 ]");
1051 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1],
1052 nullptr, nullptr));
1053 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v5 ]");
1054
1055 // clear database
1056 ASSERT_OK(Delete(1, "foo"));
1057 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1],
1058 nullptr, nullptr));
1059 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ ]");
1060
1061 // Case 5: Put followed by snapshot followed by another Put
1062 // Both puts should remain.
1063 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v6"));
1064 const Snapshot* snapshot = db_->GetSnapshot();
1065 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v7"));
1066 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1067 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v7, v6 ]");
1068 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot);
1069
1070 // clear database
1071 ASSERT_OK(Delete(1, "foo"));
1072 ASSERT_OK(dbfull()->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), handles_[1],
1073 nullptr, nullptr));
1074 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ ]");
1075
1076 // Case 5: snapshot followed by a put followed by another Put
1077 // Only the last put should remain.
1078 const Snapshot* snapshot1 = db_->GetSnapshot();
1079 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v8"));
1080 ASSERT_OK(Put(1, "foo", "v9"));
1081 ASSERT_OK(Flush(1));
1082 ASSERT_EQ(AllEntriesFor("foo", 1), "[ v9 ]");
1083 db_->ReleaseSnapshot(snapshot1);
1084 } while (ChangeCompactOptions());
1085}

1176class DBBlockChecksumTest : public DBBasicTest,

1182TEST_P(DBBlockChecksumTest, BlockChecksumTest) {
1183 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
1184 table_options.format_version = GetParam();
1185 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1186 const int kNumPerFile = 2;
1187
1188 const auto algs = GetSupportedChecksums();
1189 const int algs_size = static_cast<int>(algs.size());
1190
1191 // generate one table with each type of checksum
1192 for (int i = 0; i < algs_size; ++i) {
1193 table_options.checksum = algs[i];
1194 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1195 Reopen(options);
1196 for (int j = 0; j < kNumPerFile; ++j) {
1197 ASSERT_OK(Put(Key(i * kNumPerFile + j), Key(i * kNumPerFile + j)));
1198 }
1199 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
1200 }
1201
1202 // with each valid checksum type setting...
1203 for (int i = 0; i < algs_size; ++i) {
1204 table_options.checksum = algs[i];
1205 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
1206 Reopen(options);
1207 // verify every type of checksum (should be regardless of that setting)
1208 for (int j = 0; j < algs_size * kNumPerFile; ++j) {
1209 ASSERT_EQ(Key(j), Get(Key(j)));
1210 }
1211 }
1212
1213 // Now test invalid checksum type

1248class TestEnv : public EnvWrapper {
1249 public:
1250 explicit TestEnv(Env* base_env) : EnvWrapper(base_env), close_count(0) {}
1251 static const char* kClassName() { return "TestEnv"; }
1252 const char* Name() const override { return kClassName(); }
1253
1254 class TestLogger : public Logger {
1255 public:
1256 using Logger::Logv;
1257 explicit TestLogger(TestEnv* env_ptr) : Logger() { env = env_ptr; }
1258 ~TestLogger() override {
1259 if (!closed_) {
1260 CloseHelper().PermitUncheckedError();
1261 }
1262 }
1263 void Logv(const char* /*format*/, va_list /*ap*/) override {}
1264
1265 protected:
1266 Status CloseImpl() override { return CloseHelper(); }
1267
1268 private:
1269 Status CloseHelper() {
1270 env->CloseCountInc();
1271 ;
1272 return Status::IOError();
1273 }
1274 TestEnv* env;
1275 };
1276
1277 void CloseCountInc() { close_count++; }
1278
1279 int GetCloseCount() { return close_count; }
1280
1281 Status NewLogger(const std::string& /*fname*/,
1282 std::shared_ptr<Logger>* result) override {
1283 result->reset(new TestLogger(this));
1284 return Status::OK();
1285 }
1286
1287 private:
1288 int close_count;
1289};

1291TEST_F(DBBasicTest, DBClose) {
1292 Options options = GetDefaultOptions();
1293 std::string dbname = test::PerThreadDBPath("db_close_test");
1294 ASSERT_OK(DestroyDB(dbname, options));
1295
1296 DB* db = nullptr;
1297 TestEnv* env = new TestEnv(env_);
1298 std::unique_ptr<TestEnv> local_env_guard(env);
1299 options.create_if_missing = true;
1300 options.env = env;
1301 Status s = DB::Open(options, dbname, &db);
1302 ASSERT_OK(s);
1303 ASSERT_TRUE(db != nullptr);
1304
1305 s = db->Close();
1306 ASSERT_EQ(env->GetCloseCount(), 1);
1307 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::IOError());
1308
1309 delete db;
1310 ASSERT_EQ(env->GetCloseCount(), 1);
1311
1312 // Do not call DB::Close() and ensure our logger Close() still gets called
1313 s = DB::Open(options, dbname, &db);
1314 ASSERT_OK(s);
1315 ASSERT_TRUE(db != nullptr);
1316 delete db;
1317 ASSERT_EQ(env->GetCloseCount(), 2);
1318
1319 // close by WaitForCompact() with close_db option
1320 options.create_if_missing = false;
1321 s = DB::Open(options, dbname, &db);
1322 ASSERT_OK(s);
1323 ASSERT_TRUE(db != nullptr);
1324 WaitForCompactOptions wait_for_compact_options = WaitForCompactOptions();
1325 wait_for_compact_options.close_db = true;
1326 s = db->WaitForCompact(wait_for_compact_options);
1327 ASSERT_EQ(env->GetCloseCount(), 3);
1328 // see TestLogger::CloseHelper()
1329 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::IOError());
1330
1331 delete db;
1332 ASSERT_EQ(env->GetCloseCount(), 3);
1333
1334 // Provide our own logger and ensure DB::Close() does not close it
1335 options.info_log.reset(new TestEnv::TestLogger(env));
1336 s = DB::Open(options, dbname, &db);
1337 ASSERT_OK(s);
1338 ASSERT_TRUE(db != nullptr);
1339
1340 s = db->Close();
1341 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::OK());
1342 delete db;
1343 ASSERT_EQ(env->GetCloseCount(), 3);
1344 options.info_log.reset();
1345 ASSERT_EQ(env->GetCloseCount(), 4);
1346}

1413TEST_P(DBMultiGetTestWithParam, MultiGetMultiCF) {
1414#ifndef USE_COROUTINES
1415 if (std::get<1>(GetParam())) {
1416 ROCKSDB_GTEST_SKIP("This test requires coroutine support");
1417 return;
1418 }
1419#endif // USE_COROUTINES
1420 Options options = CurrentOptions();
1421 CreateAndReopenWithCF({"pikachu", "ilya", "muromec", "dobrynia", "nikitich",
1422 "alyosha", "popovich"},
1423 options);
1424 // <CF, key, value> tuples
1425 std::vector<std::tuple<int, std::string, std::string>> cf_kv_vec;
1426 static const int num_keys = 24;
1427 cf_kv_vec.reserve(num_keys);
1428
1429 for (int i = 0; i < num_keys; ++i) {
1430 int cf = i / 3;
1431 int cf_key = 1 % 3;
1432 cf_kv_vec.emplace_back(
1433 cf, "cf" + std::to_string(cf) + "_key_" + std::to_string(cf_key),
1434 "cf" + std::to_string(cf) + "_val_" + std::to_string(cf_key));
1435 ASSERT_OK(Put(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[i]), std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[i]),
1436 std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[i])));
1437 }
1438
1439 int get_sv_count = 0;
1440 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::DBImpl* db = static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db_);
1441 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
1442 "DBImpl::MultiCFSnapshot::AfterRefSV", [&](void* /*arg*/) {
1443 if (++get_sv_count == 2) {
1444 // After MultiGet refs a couple of CFs, flush all CFs so MultiGet
1445 // is forced to repeat the process
1446 for (int i = 0; i < num_keys; ++i) {
1447 int cf = i / 3;
1448 int cf_key = i % 8;
1449 if (cf_key == 0) {
1450 ASSERT_OK(Flush(cf));
1451 }
1452 ASSERT_OK(Put(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[i]), std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[i]),
1453 std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[i]) + "_2"));
1454 }
1455 }
1456 if (get_sv_count == 11) {
1457 for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
1458 auto* cfd = static_cast_with_check<ColumnFamilyHandleImpl>(
1459 db->GetColumnFamilyHandle(i))
1460 ->cfd();
1461 ASSERT_EQ(cfd->TEST_GetLocalSV()->Get(), SuperVersion::kSVInUse);
1462 }
1463 }
1464 });
1465 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
1466
1467 std::vector<int> cfs;
1468 std::vector<std::string> keys;
1469 std::vector<std::string> values;
1470
1471 for (int i = 0; i < num_keys; ++i) {
1472 cfs.push_back(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[i]));
1473 keys.push_back(std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[i]));
1474 }
1475
1476 values = MultiGet(cfs, keys, nullptr, std::get<0>(GetParam()),
1477 std::get<1>(GetParam()));
1478 ASSERT_EQ(values.size(), num_keys);
1479 for (unsigned int j = 0; j < values.size(); ++j) {
1480 ASSERT_EQ(values[j], std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[j]) + "_2");
1481 }
1482
1483 keys.clear();
1484 cfs.clear();
1485 cfs.push_back(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[0]));
1486 keys.push_back(std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[0]));
1487 cfs.push_back(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[3]));
1488 keys.push_back(std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[3]));
1489 cfs.push_back(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[4]));
1490 keys.push_back(std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[4]));
1491 values = MultiGet(cfs, keys, nullptr, std::get<0>(GetParam()),
1492 std::get<1>(GetParam()));
1493 ASSERT_EQ(values[0], std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[0]) + "_2");
1494 ASSERT_EQ(values[1], std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[3]) + "_2");
1495 ASSERT_EQ(values[2], std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[4]) + "_2");
1496
1497 keys.clear();
1498 cfs.clear();
1499 cfs.push_back(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[7]));
1500 keys.push_back(std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[7]));
1501 cfs.push_back(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[6]));
1502 keys.push_back(std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[6]));
1503 cfs.push_back(std::get<0>(cf_kv_vec[1]));
1504 keys.push_back(std::get<1>(cf_kv_vec[1]));
1505 values = MultiGet(cfs, keys, nullptr, std::get<0>(GetParam()),
1506 std::get<1>(GetParam()));
1507 ASSERT_EQ(values[0], std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[7]) + "_2");
1508 ASSERT_EQ(values[1], std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[6]) + "_2");
1509 ASSERT_EQ(values[2], std::get<2>(cf_kv_vec[1]) + "_2");
1510
1511 for (int cf = 0; cf < 8; ++cf) {
1512 auto* cfd =
1513 static_cast_with_check<ColumnFamilyHandleImpl>(
1514 static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db_)->GetColumnFamilyHandle(cf))
1515 ->cfd();
1516 ASSERT_NE(cfd->TEST_GetLocalSV()->Get(), SuperVersion::kSVInUse);
1517 ASSERT_NE(cfd->TEST_GetLocalSV()->Get(), SuperVersion::kSVObsolete);
1518 }
1519}

1560 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency({
1561 {"DBImpl::MultiCFSnapshot::AfterLastTryRefSV",
1562 "DBMultiGetTestWithParam::MultiGetMultiCFMutex:BeforeCreateSV"},
1563 {"DBMultiGetTestWithParam::MultiGetMultiCFMutex:AfterCreateSV",
1564 "DBImpl::MultiCFSnapshot::BeforeLastTryUnRefSV"},
1565 });
1566 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
1567
1568 port::Thread create_sv_thread([this]() {
1569 TEST_SYNC_POINT(
1570 "DBMultiGetTestWithParam::MultiGetMultiCFMutex:BeforeCreateSV");
1571 // Create a new SuperVersion for each column family after last_try
1572 // of MultiGet ref SuperVersion and before unref it.
1573 for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
1574 ASSERT_OK(Put(i, "cf" + std::to_string(i) + "_key",
1575 "cf" + std::to_string(i) + "_val_after_last_try"));
1576 ASSERT_OK(Flush(i));
1577 }
1578 TEST_SYNC_POINT(
1579 "DBMultiGetTestWithParam::MultiGetMultiCFMutex:AfterCreateSV");
1580 });
1581
1582 std::vector<int> cfs;
1583 std::vector<std::string> keys;
1584 std::vector<std::string> values;
1585
1586 for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
1587 cfs.push_back(i);
1588 keys.push_back("cf" + std::to_string(i) + "_key");
1589 }
1590
1591 values = MultiGet(cfs, keys, nullptr, std::get<0>(GetParam()),
1592 std::get<1>(GetParam()));
1593 create_sv_thread.join();
1594 ASSERT_TRUE(last_try);
1595 ASSERT_EQ(values.size(), 8);
1596 for (unsigned int j = 0; j < values.size(); ++j) {
1597 ASSERT_EQ(values[j],
1598 "cf" + std::to_string(j) + "_val" + std::to_string(retries));
1599 }
1600 for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
1601 auto* cfd =
1602 static_cast_with_check<ColumnFamilyHandleImpl>(
1603 static_cast_with_check<DBImpl>(db_)->GetColumnFamilyHandle(i))
1604 ->cfd();
1605 ASSERT_NE(cfd->TEST_GetLocalSV()->Get(), SuperVersion::kSVInUse);
1606 }
1607 ROCKSDB_NAMESPACE::SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
1608}

2024 ASSERT_OK(Flush());

2060 ASSERT_EQ(values.size(), 2);

2062 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
2063 dbfull()->ReleaseSnapshot(snap);

2708TEST_P(DBMultiGetAsyncIOTest, GetFromL1Error) {
2709 std::vector<std::string> key_strs;
2710 std::vector<Slice> keys;
2711 std::vector<PinnableSlice> values;
2712 std::vector<Status> statuses;
2713
2714 key_strs.push_back(Key(33));
2715 key_strs.push_back(Key(54));
2716 key_strs.push_back(Key(102));
2717 keys.emplace_back(key_strs[0]);
2718 keys.emplace_back(key_strs[1]);
2719 keys.emplace_back(key_strs[2]);
2720 values.resize(keys.size());
2721 statuses.resize(keys.size());
2722
2723 int count = 0;
2724 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2725 "TableCache::GetTableReader:BeforeOpenFile", [&](void* status) {
2726 count++;
2727 // Fail the last table reader open, which is the 6th SST file
2728 // since 3 overlapping L0 files + 3 L1 files containing the keys
2729 if (count == 6) {
2730 Status* s = static_cast<Status*>(status);
2731 *s = Status::IOError();
2732 }
2733 });
2734 // DB open will create table readers unless we reduce the table cache
2735 // capacity.
2736 // SanitizeOptions will set max_open_files to minimum of 20. Table cache
2737 // is allocated with max_open_files - 10 as capacity. So override
2738 // max_open_files to 11 so table cache capacity will become 1. This will
2739 // prevent file open during DB open and force the file to be opened
2740 // during MultiGet
2741 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
2742 "SanitizeOptions::AfterChangeMaxOpenFiles", [&](void* arg) {
2743 int* max_open_files = (int*)arg;
2744 *max_open_files = 11;
2745 });
2746 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
2747
2748 PrepareDBForTest();
2749
2750 ReadOptions ro;
2751 ro.async_io = true;
2752 ro.optimize_multiget_for_io = GetParam();
2753 dbfull()->MultiGet(ro, dbfull()->DefaultColumnFamily(), keys.size(),
2754 keys.data(), values.data(), statuses.data());
2755 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
2756 ASSERT_EQ(values.size(), 3);
2757 ASSERT_EQ(statuses[0], Status::OK());
2758 ASSERT_EQ(statuses[1], Status::OK());
2759 ASSERT_EQ(statuses[2], Status::IOError());
2760
2761 HistogramData multiget_io_batch_size;
2762
2763 statistics()->histogramData(MULTIGET_IO_BATCH_SIZE, &multiget_io_batch_size);
2764
2765 // A batch of 3 async IOs is expected, one for each overlapping file in L1
2766 ASSERT_EQ(multiget_io_batch_size.count, 1);
2767 ASSERT_EQ(multiget_io_batch_size.max, 2);
2768 ASSERT_EQ(statistics()->getTickerCount(MULTIGET_COROUTINE_COUNT), 2);
2769}
2770#endif // ROCKSDB_IOURING_PRESENT

3904TEST_P(DBBasicTestTrackWal, DoNotTrackObsoleteWal) {

4506class DeadlineFS : public FileSystemWrapper {
4507 public:
4508 // The error_on_delay parameter specifies whether a IOStatus::TimedOut()
4509 // status should be returned after delaying the IO to exceed the timeout,
4510 // or to simply delay but return success anyway. The latter mimics the
4511 // behavior of PosixFileSystem, which does not enforce any timeout
4512 explicit DeadlineFS(SpecialEnv* env, bool error_on_delay)
4513 : FileSystemWrapper(env->GetFileSystem()),
4514 deadline_(std::chrono::microseconds::zero()),
4515 io_timeout_(std::chrono::microseconds::zero()),
4516 env_(env),
4517 timedout_(false),
4518 ignore_deadline_(false),
4519 error_on_delay_(error_on_delay) {}
4520
4521 static const char* kClassName() { return "DeadlineFileSystem"; }
4522 const char* Name() const override { return kClassName(); }
4523
4524 IOStatus NewRandomAccessFile(const std::string& fname,
4525 const FileOptions& opts,
4526 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile>* result,
4527 IODebugContext* dbg) override {
4528 std::unique_ptr<FSRandomAccessFile> file;
4529 IOStatus s = target()->NewRandomAccessFile(fname, opts, &file, dbg);
4530 EXPECT_OK(s);
4531 result->reset(new DeadlineRandomAccessFile(*this, file));
4532
4533 const std::chrono::microseconds deadline = GetDeadline();
4534 const std::chrono::microseconds io_timeout = GetIOTimeout();
4535 if (deadline.count() || io_timeout.count()) {
4536 AssertDeadline(deadline, io_timeout, opts.io_options);
4537 }
4538 return ShouldDelay(opts.io_options);
4539 }
4540
4541 // Set a vector of {IO counter, delay in microseconds, return status} tuples
4542 // that control when to inject a delay and duration of the delay
4543 void SetDelayTrigger(const std::chrono::microseconds deadline,
4544 const std::chrono::microseconds io_timeout,
4545 const int trigger) {
4546 delay_trigger_ = trigger;
4547 io_count_ = 0;
4548 deadline_ = deadline;
4549 io_timeout_ = io_timeout;
4550 timedout_ = false;
4551 }
4552
4553 // Increment the IO counter and return a delay in microseconds
4554 IOStatus ShouldDelay(const IOOptions& opts) {
4555 if (timedout_) {
4556 return IOStatus::TimedOut();
4557 } else if (!deadline_.count() && !io_timeout_.count()) {
4558 return IOStatus::OK();
4559 }
4560 if (!ignore_deadline_ && delay_trigger_ == io_count_++) {
4561 env_->SleepForMicroseconds(static_cast<int>(opts.timeout.count() + 1));
4562 timedout_ = true;
4563 if (error_on_delay_) {
4564 return IOStatus::TimedOut();
4565 }
4566 }
4567 return IOStatus::OK();
4568 }
4569
4570 const std::chrono::microseconds GetDeadline() {
4571 return ignore_deadline_ ? std::chrono::microseconds::zero() : deadline_;
4572 }
4573
4574 const std::chrono::microseconds GetIOTimeout() {
4575 return ignore_deadline_ ? std::chrono::microseconds::zero() : io_timeout_;
4576 }
4577
4578 bool TimedOut() { return timedout_; }
4579
4580 void IgnoreDeadline(bool ignore) { ignore_deadline_ = ignore; }
4581
4582 void AssertDeadline(const std::chrono::microseconds deadline,
4583 const std::chrono::microseconds io_timeout,
4584 const IOOptions& opts) const {
4585 // Give a leeway of +- 10us as it can take some time for the Get/
4586 // MultiGet call to reach here, in order to avoid false alarms
4587 std::chrono::microseconds now =
4588 std::chrono::microseconds(env_->NowMicros());
4589 std::chrono::microseconds timeout;
4590 if (deadline.count()) {
4591 timeout = deadline - now;
4592 if (io_timeout.count()) {
4593 timeout = std::min(timeout, io_timeout);
4594 }
4595 } else {
4596 timeout = io_timeout;
4597 }
4598 if (opts.timeout != timeout) {
4599 ASSERT_EQ(timeout, opts.timeout);
4600 }
4601 }
4602
4603 private:
4604 // The number of IOs to trigger the delay after
4605 int delay_trigger_;
4606 // Current IO count
4607 int io_count_;
4608 // ReadOptions deadline for the Get/MultiGet/Iterator
4609 std::chrono::microseconds deadline_;
4610 // ReadOptions io_timeout for the Get/MultiGet/Iterator
4611 std::chrono::microseconds io_timeout_;
4612 SpecialEnv* env_;
4613 // Flag to indicate whether we injected a delay
4614 bool timedout_;
4615 // Temporarily ignore deadlines/timeouts
4616 bool ignore_deadline_;
4617 // Return IOStatus::TimedOut() or IOStatus::OK()
4618 bool error_on_delay_;
4619};

4724 // Test batched MultiGet with an IO delay in the first data block read.
4725 // Both keys in the first CF should succeed as they're in the same data
4726 // block and would form one batch, and we check for deadline between
4727 // batches.
4728 std::vector<std::string> key_str;
4729 size_t i;
4730 for (i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
4731 key_str.emplace_back(Key(static_cast<int>(i)));

4734 std::vector<Slice> keys(key_str.size());
4735 std::vector<PinnableSlice> pin_values(keys.size());
4736
4737 for (i = 0; i < key_str.size(); ++i) {
4738 // 2 keys per CF
4739 cfs[i] = handles_[i / 2];
4740 keys[i] = Slice(key_str[i].data(), key_str[i].size());
4741 }

4743 ro.deadline = std::chrono::microseconds{env->NowMicros() + 10000};
4744 ro.async_io = GetParam();

4747

4750 pin_values.data(), statuses.data());
4751 // The first key is successful because we check after the lookup, but
4752 // subsequent keys fail due to deadline exceeded
4753 CheckStatus(statuses, 2);
4754
4755 // Similar to the previous one, but an IO delay in the third CF data block
4756 // read
4757 for (PinnableSlice& value : pin_values) {
4758 value.Reset();
4759 }
4760 cache->SetCapacity(0);
4761 cache->SetCapacity(1048576);
4762 statuses.clear();
4763 statuses.resize(keys.size());
4764 ro.deadline = std::chrono::microseconds{env->NowMicros() + 10000};
4765 fs->SetDelayTrigger(ro.deadline, ro.io_timeout, 2);
4766 dbfull()->MultiGet(ro, keys.size(), cfs.data(), keys.data(),
4767 pin_values.data(), statuses.data());
4768 CheckStatus(statuses, 6);
4769
4770 // Similar to the previous one, but an IO delay in the last but one CF
4771 for (PinnableSlice& value : pin_values) {
4772 value.Reset();
4773 }
4774 cache->SetCapacity(0);
4775 cache->SetCapacity(1048576);
4776 statuses.clear();
4777 statuses.resize(keys.size());
4778 ro.deadline = std::chrono::microseconds{env->NowMicros() + 10000};
4779 fs->SetDelayTrigger(ro.deadline, ro.io_timeout, 3);
4780 dbfull()->MultiGet(ro, keys.size(), cfs.data(), keys.data(),
4781 pin_values.data(), statuses.data());
4782 CheckStatus(statuses, 8);
4783
4784 // Test batched MultiGet with single CF and lots of keys. Inject delay
4785 // into the second batch of keys. As each batch is 32, the first 64 keys,
4786 // i.e first two batches, should succeed and the rest should time out
4787 for (PinnableSlice& value : pin_values) {
4788 value.Reset();
4789 }
4790 cache->SetCapacity(0);
4791 cache->SetCapacity(1048576);
4792 key_str.clear();
4793 for (i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {
4794 key_str.emplace_back(Key(static_cast<int>(i)));
4795 }
4796 keys.resize(key_str.size());
4797 pin_values.clear();
4798 pin_values.resize(key_str.size());
4799 for (i = 0; i < key_str.size(); ++i) {
4800 keys[i] = Slice(key_str[i].data(), key_str[i].size());
4801 }
4802 statuses.clear();
4803 statuses.resize(keys.size());
4804 ro.deadline = std::chrono::microseconds{env->NowMicros() + 10000};
4805 fs->SetDelayTrigger(ro.deadline, ro.io_timeout, 1);
4806 dbfull()->MultiGet(ro, handles_[0], keys.size(), keys.data(),

5028TEST_P(DBBasicTestDeadline, PointLookupDeadline) {
5029 std::shared_ptr<DeadlineFS> fs = std::make_shared<DeadlineFS>(env_, true);
5030 std::unique_ptr<Env> env(new CompositeEnvWrapper(env_, fs));
5031 bool set_deadline = std::get<0>(GetParam());
5032 bool set_timeout = std::get<1>(GetParam());
5033
5034 for (int option_config = kDefault; option_config < kEnd; ++option_config) {
5035 if (ShouldSkipOptions(option_config, kSkipPlainTable | kSkipMmapReads)) {
5036 continue;
5037 }
5038 option_config_ = option_config;
5039 Options options = CurrentOptions();
5040 if (options.use_direct_reads) {
5041 continue;
5042 }
5043 options.env = env.get();
5044 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
5045 Cache* block_cache = nullptr;
5046 // Fileter block reads currently don't cause the request to get
5047 // aborted on a read timeout, so its possible those block reads
5048 // may get issued even if the deadline is past
5049 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
5050 "BlockBasedTable::Get:BeforeFilterMatch",
5051 [&](void* /*arg*/) { fs->IgnoreDeadline(true); });
5052 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
5053 "BlockBasedTable::Get:AfterFilterMatch",
5054 [&](void* /*arg*/) { fs->IgnoreDeadline(false); });
5055 // DB open will create table readers unless we reduce the table cache
5056 // capacity.
5057 // SanitizeOptions will set max_open_files to minimum of 20. Table cache
5058 // is allocated with max_open_files - 10 as capacity. So override
5059 // max_open_files to 11 so table cache capacity will become 1. This will
5060 // prevent file open during DB open and force the file to be opened
5061 // during MultiGet
5062 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
5063 "SanitizeOptions::AfterChangeMaxOpenFiles", [&](void* arg) {
5064 int* max_open_files = (int*)arg;
5065 *max_open_files = 11;
5066 });
5067 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
5068
5069 SetTimeElapseOnlySleepOnReopen(&options);
5070 Reopen(options);
5071
5072 if (options.table_factory) {
5073 block_cache = options.table_factory->GetOptions<Cache>(
5074 TableFactory::kBlockCacheOpts());
5075 }
5076
5077 Random rnd(301);
5078 for (int i = 0; i < 400; ++i) {
5079 std::string key = "k" + std::to_string(i);
5080 ASSERT_OK(Put(key, rnd.RandomString(100)));
5081 }
5082 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
5083
5084 bool timedout = true;
5085 // A timeout will be forced when the IO counter reaches this value
5086 int io_deadline_trigger = 0;
5087 // Keep incrementing io_deadline_trigger and call Get() until there is an
5088 // iteration that doesn't cause a timeout. This ensures that we cover
5089 // all file reads in the point lookup path that can potentially timeout
5090 // and cause the Get() to fail.
5091 while (timedout) {
5092 ReadOptions ro;
5093 if (set_deadline) {
5094 ro.deadline = std::chrono::microseconds{env->NowMicros() + 10000};
5095 }
5096 if (set_timeout) {
5097 ro.io_timeout = std::chrono::microseconds{5000};
5098 }
5099 fs->SetDelayTrigger(ro.deadline, ro.io_timeout, io_deadline_trigger);
5100
5101 block_cache->SetCapacity(0);
5102 block_cache->SetCapacity(1048576);
5103
5104 std::string value;
5105 Status s = dbfull()->Get(ro, "k50", &value);
5106 if (fs->TimedOut()) {
5107 ASSERT_EQ(s, Status::TimedOut());
5108 } else {
5109 timedout = false;
5110 ASSERT_OK(s);
5111 }
5112 io_deadline_trigger++;
5113 }
5114 // Reset the delay sequence in order to avoid false alarms during Reopen
5115 fs->SetDelayTrigger(std::chrono::microseconds::zero(),
5116 std::chrono::microseconds::zero(), 0);
5117 }
5118 Close();
5119}
